B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026        FY 2027
This funding will further refine Developmental Engineering efforts to include but not limited to Manned Unmanned Teaming (MUM-
T) Protected Comms, Advanced Combat Vehicle Concepts, Autonomous Vehicles, Advanced Combat Vehicle Concepts, Combat
Vehicle Light-weighting, Compound Eye, Vehicle Excursions, Aided Target Detection and Recognition (AiTDR), Threat Warning
Sensor integration, Segmented Composite Rubber Track (S-CRT), Virtual Operator/Maintainer, Active Protection System Sensing
(APS) and other combat vehicle technology advancement efforts. These advanced development efforts will include performance
analysis, trade space analysis, capabilities assessments, and hardware demonstrations to support the emerging technologies to
support the Army's Modernization Strategy. Additionally, include the maturation of the Ground Common Infrastructure Architecture
(GCIA), Small Form Factor Common Compute, data architecture and open architecture standards.
FY 2027 Plans:
This funding will further refine Developmental Engineering efforts to include but not limited to Advanced Combat Vehicle
Concepts, enable faster prototyping and fielding of critical capabilities, integrate emerging technology into formations to innovate,
and refine requirements with Vehicle Excursions, Aided Target Detection and Recognition (AiTDR), Segmented Composite
Rubber Track (S-CRT), Vehicle Base Kits (VBK) Gen 3, Virtual Operator/Maintainer, Virtual Fielder, Active Protection System
Sensing (APS) and other combat vehicle technology advancement efforts. These advanced development efforts will include
performance analysis, trade space analysis, capabilities assessments, and hardware demonstrations to support the emerging
technologies to support the Army's Modernization Strategy. Additionally, include the maturation of the Ground Common
Infrastructure Architecture (GCIA), Small Form Factor Common Compute, data architecture and open architecture standards.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding increase is due to continuing activities for Advanced Combat Vehicle Concepts efforts, Virtual Operator/
Maintainer, Virtual Fielder, the maturation of the Ground Common Infrastructure Architecture (GCIA), Small Form Factor Common
Compute, and Vehicle Excursions while initiating activities for Aided Target Detection and Recognition (AiTDR), Segmented
Composite Rubber Track (S-CRT), Vehicle Base Kits (VBK) Gen 3, and other activities.
Title: Test & Evaluation                                                                                                                  12.279       9.626           1.000
Description: Test and Evaluation (T&E) activities include contractor and government testing of prototype vehicles and
technologies as well as user evaluations. Testing will be conducted using United States Army test facilities.

FY 2026 Plans:
This funding includes test and evaluation efforts to MUM-T Protected Comms, Combat Vehicle Light-weighting, Compound Eye,
Aided Target Detection and Recognition (AiTDR), Segmented Composite Rubber Track (S-CRT), XM913 testing, Virtual Operator/
Maintainer, Active Protection System Sensing (APS) and other emerging combat vehicle technology advancements to assist

