Description: This effort looks to research updated grounding and bonding techniques based on existing and new technologies
being developed by the US Army to better support specific systems/platforms integration and operational testing for advanced
mobile and tactical ground systems. This is critical for safety of both personnel and equipment. The study will review current MIL-
STDs, pamphlets, Technical Manuals (TM), policies and new/future power systems to generate an alternative policy guidance
