A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Program Element (PE) provides analytical support of Analysis of Alternatives (AoAs). AoAs are statutory requirements for MDAPs and regulatory for all other
programs. Based on Department of Defense Instruction (DoDI) 5000.84, AoAs are required to be initiated after the Materiel Development Decision (MDD) to identify the
best value materiel solution. The project provides analytical capability for Pre-Milestone A programs that emerge outside the normal budget or POM cycles. Normally
these programs are without program managers and require analysis to support Congressional, Department of War (DoW) and Army Senior Leader's requirement and
acquisition needs and priorities. The AoAs support the development of requirements, Key Performance Parameters and thresholds values and tradeoff analysis. The
cited work is consistent with the Army Science and Technology priority focus areas and the Army Transformation Initiative (ATI). The Army will assess and fund the
highest Congressional, DoW, and Army Senior Leader's priorities during the year of execution.

