products to a goal of TRL 7, integrating them into technology demonstrators and experimental prototypes for Army Service Component Commands, Army Corps, Army
Divisions and below. This initiative streamlines the development and insertion of mature technologies that support ground and air maneuver; fires; command and control
(C2) and counter C2; agile sustainment and ammunition; and layered protection plus chemical, biological, radiological, and nuclear.
It provides the Army an improved mechanism for rapidly incorporating innovative technologies and advanced capabilities to support Secretary of War and Secretary of
the Army Acquisition Reform efforts.

 This PE also provides a tiered evaluation and feasibility application of innovative and disruptive technologies to Army capability gaps at any stage in a technology's
 lifecycle. The project will partner with academia, small, non-traditional companies, and the defense industrial base to incubate ideas, stage pilot evaluations and to
 ensure more rapid integration and prototyping of the best, most innovative solutions into Army systems.

 Project teams comprised of both Technology Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) and Acquisition Program leads to develop the project concept, execute the program,
 fabricate and evaluate the prototype, and develop the path to scale for incorporating the technology upon successful evaluation of the prototype.

