Will prototype capabilities supporting command and control systems/subsystems and position, navigation, and timing systems.
Specific plans include a C2 effort that will complement investments with the U.S. Army Close Terrain Shaping Obstacle program
by leveraging recent developments in advanced communication waveforms to enable fully networked Command and Control anti-
vehicle munitions.
FY 2027 Plans:
Will focus on prototyping advanced capabilities for command and control (C2) systems/subsystems and position, navigation,
and timing (PNT) systems to enhance operational effectiveness. Specific plans include developing a C2 effort that complements
investments in the U.S. Army Close Terrain Shaping Obstacle program by leveraging recent advancements in communication
waveforms to enable fully networked Command and Control for anti-vehicle munitions. Additionally, new waveforms will be
developed to improve communication resilience, expand network interoperability, and ensure reliable performance in contested
environments.
