D. Acquisition Strategy
The APNT Modernization develops prototypes for a scalable/tiered PNT solutions for clients and vehicular platforms. APNT Modernization will fully implement a Modular
Open Systems Approach (MOSA), support future integration of Military GPS User Equipment (MGUE) Increment 2, and improve complimentary PNT capabilities that
provides a layered, accurate position and time in the absence of GPS for extended missions. The acquisition strategy for the APNT Modernization effort employs a dual-
vendor approach for its prototyping phase. This initiative leverages a competitively awarded Other Transaction Authority (OTA) agreement to foster robust competition.
The two vendors were selected based on their white paper submissions and subsequent technical demonstrations. Upon successful completion of this OTA phase, the
government is authorized to award a follow-on production contract or transaction to one of the vendors without requiring further competitive procedures.




