D. Acquisition Strategy
The Dismounted Assured PNT (APNT) System (DAPS) acquisition strategy consists of an iterative development security operations (DevSecOps) methodology
for the development, testing, production and fielding of a material solution that implements Congressional guidance for M-Code capability (10 USC 2281), Modular
Open Systems Approach (Reference House Report 116-442, 2020), and the DAPS Capability Development Document (CDD) (signed 28 January 2022) performance
requirements. The DAPS strategy leverages competitive Other Transaction Authority (OTA) agreements and Small Business Innovative Research (SBIR) contracts
to assess industry capabilities, develop prototypes, and mature technology upgrades. Developmental test and operational assessment results informed a best value


