Unmanned Aerial Systems (C-sUAS). JIATF 401 synchronizes C-UAS efforts across the DoW to rapidly deliver joint capabilities at scale to defend the homeland, protect
US and allied forces, defend critical infrastructure, and assist federal agencies. The task force has a global focus and is a multifaceted organization leading DoW C-
sUAS activities at the nexus of OSW, the Joint Staff, Combatant Commands, and the Services. The JIATF 401 is innovative, scalable, and threat adaptive. We have
one measure of effectiveness: quickly deliver state of the art c-UAS capability to the warfighter at home and abroad. The Secretary of War (SecWar) designated the
Secretary of the Army (SA) as the DoW's Executive Agent (EA) for Counter-small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS) and aligned the JIATF 401 as a Chairmans
Controlled Activity (CCA)in the Joint Staff. The EA holds the acquisition and procurement authority and oversight for the JIATF 401 efforts. All resources are being
transferred to 0205401JCA.

